description: In recent years, Tianjin's cauliflower seed exports to Pakistan have accounted for over 70 percent of Pakistan's annual planting, helping to address bottlenecks in the local cauliflower industry.
title: Tianjin's cauliflower seeds help address local industrial bottlenecks in Pakistan

description: TEHRAN – The Persian translation of the book “The Psychology of Counselling” written by Marie Percival has been released in the bookstores across Iran.
title: “The Psychology of Counselling” published in Persian

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian short film “Ramy” written and directed by Pouyan Rostami and produced by Kasra Tirsahar will have its world premiere at the 2025 Cindependent Film Festival in Cincinnati, Ohio, the U.S., which will be held from September 18 to 20.
title: Cindependent Film Festival will screen Iranian short film “Ramy”

description: TEHRAN – Renowned Iranian vocalist Homayoun Shajarian will hold a free outdoor concert on Friday at Azadi Square in Tehran.
title: Homayoun Shajarian to hold free outdoor concert at Azadi Square

description: TEHRAN - In a note, the Iran newspaper addressed President Masoud Pezeshkian's presence at the Shanghai Cooperation Organization (SCO) Summit in Tianjin and wrote: The presence of the Iranian president in the SCO summit is more important than others in many respects.
title: Iran's diplomatic power after the war

description: President Masoud Pezeshkian, during his visit to Beijing, highlighted Iran's ongoing struggle against biased international scrutiny. Speaking to China Central Television (CCTV), he underscored the unfair treatment Iran receives from the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), a reflection of larger double standards created by the West.
title: President calls for fair global order in interview with Chinese media

description: TEHRAN – President Masoud Pezeshkian arrived in China on Monday for a four-day official visit, the longest by an Iranian leader to the country. The visit is expected to strengthen economic and security ties between the two nations, and potentially deliver key benefits for Iran.
title: The lion-dragon synergy

description: MADRID – The 25th Summit of the Shanghai Cooperation Organization (SCO), held in Tianjin, China, marks a significant moment for Iran and its regional strategy.
title: Iran and the SCO: A measured turn in Asian geopolitics

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Foreign Ministry has rejected claims that Tehran failed to meet its commitments under the 2015 nuclear deal (JCPOA), saying the parties that neglected their obligations have no right to accuse Iran of inaction.
title: Negligent JCPOA parties cannot accuse Tehran of inaction: Iran foreign ministry

description: TEHRAN – Iran has strongly reiterated its sovereignty over the three Persian Gulf islands—Abu Musa, Greater Tunb, and Lesser Tunb—its rights to the Arash gas field, and the peaceful nature of its nuclear program, responding to recent claims by the Persian Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC).
title: Iran denounces Arab states’ claim to Persian Gulf Islands, Arash gas field

description: TEHRAN – The recent statement by the foreign ministers of the three European countries—Britain, France, and Germany—regarding the activation of the so-called “Snapback” mechanism against the Islamic Republic of Iran is yet another attempt to exert political and legal pressure on a country that has not only never initiated any war in its modern history but has also been the direct victim of aggressions and repeated violations of commitments by Western powers.
title: How Europe is bullying Iran in the name of global peace

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s top security official said the path for dialogue with the United States remains open, but Washington’s refusal to engage seriously is preventing the parties from entering new talks.
title: Iran is ready for talks, but US missile demands are obstructing progress, says Larijani

description: TEHRAN – The recent deployment of United States military forces in the waters off Venezuela has reignited concerns over Washington’s long history of interventions and regime-change policies in Latin America and the Caribbean. The move comes amid US claims that the deployment is intended to combat threats from regional drug cartels.
title: US strategy in Venezuela stirs regional alarm, echoes Bolton’s coup revelations

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Parliament Speaker Mohammad Baqer Qalibaf on Tuesday denounced the European troika’s decision to trigger the snapback mechanism of sanctions as “illegal” and vowed that the Islamic Republic will soon announce a unified and decisive response.
title: Parliament ponders response options to E3’s ‘snapback’ push

description: TEHRAN – On September 1, more than 250 news outlets in over 70 countries staged a coordinated blackout—blank front pages, darkened homepages, and interrupted broadcasts—in an unprecedented act of solidarity.
title: Over 250 media outlets unite as Israel makes Gaza’s journalists its frontline targets

description: JOHANNESBURG – The first day of the BRICS Summer School unfolded with a sense of urgency in the city of Johannesburg in South Africa. Scholars and young leaders from across the Global South gathered to discuss alternative narratives in international relations, the deepening of intra-BRICS cooperation, and the role of youth in shaping the future of this rapidly evolving bloc.
title: BRICS Summer School opens with calls for alternative narratives

description: BEIRUT—Writing in The Telegraph, former U.S. National Security Advisor John Bolton has said “Hezbollah shows no signs of giving up.  And, for well or ill, the UN’s longstanding Lebanon peacekeeping mission, UNIFIL, has such a tarnished reputation for ineffectiveness that its mandate will be ended at the end of 2026.”
title: Lebanon’s future, one year after the US–led Israeli aggression
President Xi: China-Russia relationship model of major-country ties

description: TEHRAN - The stage is set for a crucial encounter as Iran’s U23 football team, affectionately known as "Team Omid," prepare to kick off its 2026 AFC U23 Championship qualifiers.
title: A new chapter for Iran's U23: can they end the Olympic drought?

description: TEHRAN – Ghafour Kargari, president of Iran’s National Paralympic Committee (NPC), says the Asian Youth Para Games 2025 are a valuable opportunity to identify talented athletes for the 2026 Asian Para Games and the 2028 Paralympic Games.
title: Asian Youth Para Games a chance to unearth new talents: Kargari

description: TEHRAN—Chogha Golan region in Mehran county, Ilam province, is the oldest cradle of agriculture across Iran and West Asia, Habibollah Mahmoudian, a specialist in prehistoric archaeology, has said.
title: Ilam’s Chogha Golan, the oldest agricultural origin in West Asia

description: TEHRAN – A new phase of restoration has been commenced on the historic walls and towers of Damghan, a city in Semnan province known for its ancient fortifications and cultural heritage, an official said on Sunday.
title: Damghan’s historic fortifications undergo restoration

description: TEHRAN— Hojjatollah Ayyubi, who heads the Tourism Ministry’s Center for International Affairs, arrived Bali on Monday to attend Chandi Summit 2025, which will take place from September 3-5, 2025, at the Bali Beach Convention.
title: Iran attends Chandi Summit 2025 in Indonesia

description: TEHRAN— An enormous tourism festival in Isfahan has commenced to highlight the endless charms of the province, whose capital of the same name was the seat of power in the 17th century.
title: Isfahan tourism festival begins with 90 events

description: TEHRAN – Iran will take center stage in the first phase of a new museum dedicated to international entrepreneurs being built in Dubai, with busts of 20 Iranian business leaders to be installed, the United Network of Business Entrepreneurs and Development Organization (UNBEDO) said.
title: Dubai museum project to spotlight 20 Iranian entrepreneurs in first phase

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s president is expected to leverage the Shanghai Cooperation Organization (SCO) leaders’ summit in China to expand the country’s trade opportunities, the head of the Iran-China Joint Chamber of Commerce said.
title: Tehran eyes trade boost from Pezeshkian’s participation in SCO summit

description: TEHRAN – Cooperatives represent not only an economic model but also a practical philosophy for achieving equitable growth and sustainable development, the head of Iran Chamber of Cooperatives (ICC) said on Tuesday.
title: ICC chief says cooperatives key to fair growth, sustainable development

description: TEHRAN – Iran is finalizing a comprehensive management and conservation plan for Persepolis, a UNESCO World Heritage site in Fars province, amid growing concerns from experts about erosion of its ancient stone reliefs, the site’s director said.
title: Effort underway to safeguard Persepolis from ongoing erosion

description: TEHRAN – Iran inaugurated its largest rooftop solar power plant on Tuesday in the Chenaran industrial town of Khorasan Razavi Province, with a capacity of 4.5 megawatts, provincial officials said.
title: Iran opens largest rooftop solar power plant in Khorasan Razavi

description: TEHRAN – The Palestinian resistance continues its operations against the Israeli occupation’s infantry trying to invade Gaza City via the Zeitoun neighborhood.
title: Israeli vehicles struck in Gaza City

description: A powerful 6.0-magnitude earthquake struck eastern Afghanistan just past midnight on Sunday, triggering one of the deadliest disasters in recent memory.
title: Death toll surpasses 1,400 as Afghanistan reels from quake

description: TEHRAN – Iran exported non-oil goods worth $20.92 billion in the first five months of the current Iranian year (March 21-August 22), accounting for more than 61 million tons of shipments, the head of the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) said.
title: Iran’s non-oil exports nears $21b in 5 months

description: Hundreds have died after a landslide buried the village of Tarseen in Sudan’s Marra Mountains, officials and aid agencies said.
title: Hundreds killed in Sudan landslide as entire village erased

description: The time is ripe for harvesting pistachios from the end of summer to the start of autumn in the northeastern province of North Khorasan.
title: Pistachio harvest in northeastern Iran

description: TEHRAN - Jack Shiratani and Zen Hawkins starred as Japan trounced Iran 86-67 to book the first ticket to the FIBA U16 Asia Cup 2025 Quarter-Finals, Tuesday at the MBank Arena.
title: Iran lose to Japan at FIBA U16 Asia Cup 2025

description: TEHRAN – The winners of the 6th Mustafa (PBUH) Prize were announced on Tuesday in a press briefing held at the secretariat of the Mustafa Prize in Tehran.
title: Mustafa Prize 2025 announces winners

description: TEHRAN – The head of the Iranian Red Crescent Society (IRCS), Pirhossein Kolivand, has announced readiness to send relief supplies and rescue forces to assist people impacted by the earthquake in Afghanistan.
title: IRCS ready to aid quake-hit Afghanistan

description: TEHRAN – The United Nations Children’s Fund (UNICEF) has procured large consignments of rabies, pentavalent, and rotavirus vaccines to immunize children against life-threatening diseases.
title: UNICEF supplies Iran with rabies, pentavalent, and rotavirus vaccines

description: TEHRAN -A total of 101 earthquakes were recorded across the country in a week from August 23 to 29, according to the seismological networks of the Institute of Geophysics of the University of Tehran.
title: Over 100 earthquakes hit Iran in a week

description: TEHRAN - The Iranian U21 men's national volleyball team have once again cemented their status as a global powerhouses, securing a historic third consecutive World Championship title with an undefeated run at the 2025 FIVB tournament in Jiangmen, China.
title: Undefeated & Unstoppable: Iran's golden generation dominates world stage

description: TEHRAN- In recent days, the entire nation of Viet Nam is joyfully celebrating the 80th anniversary of National Day (September 2nd, 1945 – September 2nd, 2025). On this occasion, the Embassy of the Socialist Republic of Viet Nam in the Islamic Republic of Iran respectfully presents to our Iranian friends an overview of the 80-year journey of struggle for independence, safeguarding of peace, and the process of nation-building and development of Viet Nam.
title: Viet Nam – 80 Years of Journey for National Independence, Peace, and Development

description: A 38-page plan circulating in the Trump administration outlines a U.S.-run trusteeship for postwar Gaza, proposing to transform the devastated enclave into a hub of luxury resorts and technology industries — while uprooting millions of Palestinians in the process.
title: Washington Post exposes Trump’s Gaza ‘GREAT Trust’ plan as displacement scheme

description: TEHRAN — While Israeli officials publicly insist that Operation Gideon’s Chariots, a major May ground and air offensive aimed at defeating Hamas, freeing Israeli captives, and seizing control over most of the Gaza Strip, was a success, newly leaked internal documents from the Israeli military tell a very different story.
title: Leaked Israeli documents reveal total failure of 'Gideon’s Chariots' operation

description: TEHRAN – The Yemeni Armed Forces announced on Monday that they had carried out a ballistic missile strike on the SCARLET RAY, an Israeli oil tanker in the northern Red Sea, in response to the regime’s deadly Thursday attack on a cabinet meeting in Sanaa.
title: Yemen strikes Israeli oil tanker

description: BEIRUT — Yemen’s Prime Minister Ahmed Ghaleb al-Rahwi was martyred, along with several ministers who were either killed or wounded, in a raid by the Zionist regime on a government headquarters in Sana’a last Thursday.
title: Yemen sacrifices PM and ministers for Palestinians
